==English==
===Etymology===
Mediaeval Latin, from Arabic {{ARchar|[[قالنجان]]}} (qālanjān) (cognate with Persian {{FAchar|[[قولنجان]]}} (kūlinjān), Sanskrit [[कुलञ्जन]]), perhaps from Chinese ''gāoliángjiāng'', from ''gāoliáng'' (a district in China) + [[薑]] (jiāng) ‘ginger’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /gə'læŋgə/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|galanga|galangas}}
# any of several east Asian plants of the [[ginger]] family, used as a spice

